<p>Another common error is making names too long or difficult to pronounce. If your players or readers cannot say the name out loud, they will abbreviate it or worse, mock it. A kingdom called Xzythryllian'athar is memorable for all the wrong reasons. Aim for names that are distinct but pronounceable on first encounter.</p>
